1.    Populate and align the charts appropriately

a.    Regional Part D Penetration Rate and Patient Cost

                                          i.    Add the 1.AnnualCostPerPatient measure to “Line values”

                                        ii.    Add the 4.PatientPenetrationRate measure to “Column values”

                                       iii.    Add the Region column to “Shared Axis”

                                       iv.    Click on the “General” dropdown and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

b.    Patient Cost

                                          i.    Add the 1.AnnualCostPerPatient measure to “Column values”

                                        ii.    Add the 2.YoY%CostPerPatient measure to “Line values”

                                       iii.    Add the Year column to “Shared Axis”

                                        v.    Click on the “General” dropdown and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

c.    Yearly Part D Penetration Rate and YoY Retention

                                          i.    Add the 4.PatientPenetrationRate measure to “Column values”

                                        ii.    Add the 5.YoY%PatientRetention measure to “Line values”

                                       iii.    Add the Year column to “Shared Axis”

                                       iv.    Click on the “General” dropdown and adjust the dimensions as shown on the GIF below:

                                        v.    Update the “Titles” and “Legends”  for the Regional Part D Penetration Rate and Patient Cost visual as indicated on the GIF below:
